translations.name: Westminster Bible
translations.description: The Westminster Bible is a translation of the Christian Bible produced by the Roman Catholics of Great Britain between 1913 and 1935. The General Editors were Cuthbert Lattey and Joseph Keating. A complete Bible with the New Testament and Psalms in the Westminster Version and the remainder in the Challoner's revision of the Douay-Rheims Version was printed in 1958 with a second edition in 1966.
